value.name: .338 Lapua Magnum - Wikipedia
value.snippet: The .338 Lapua Magnum (8.6×70 mm or 8.58×70 mm) is a rimless, bottlenecked, centerfire rifle cartridge. It was developed during the 1980s as a high-powered, long-range cartridge for military snipers. It was used in the War in Afghanistan and the Iraq War. As a result of this, it has become widely available.

value.name: .338 Winchester Magnum - Wikipedia
